CatDescriptText: Mrs. Alice Butler, clerk, 2229 Ishar Way, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 28, 1959, pg. A1, with question: "Do you think the morals of the community are better than they used to be, worse or about the same? If there is any change, what do you think caused it?" answer reads: "I think that they are a little different, and this change is for the better."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Alice Butler wearing light colored coat with belt and plush collar, striped button down collared shirt, and hoop earrings, standing in front of swirled granite wall and Lutheran Church Supply Store sign, Wood Street, Downtown
